Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper proposes a game-theoretic model for the formation of signed networks among members of a social network. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper presents a game-theoretic analysis of the proposed network formation game. 
3. cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) - The paper deals with the formation of social networks and their properties. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a model for the formation of networks and analyzes its properties. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with the behavior of multiple agents in a network formation game.
